    Scope and Contents
Hobart Heistand, Episcopal minister, discusses his work at the Christ Episcopal Church in Springfield, changes in the prayer book, ministerial duties, counselling, clergy and the congregation, services, and changes in the church, religion, and society. He also discusses growing up in Pennsylvania as the son of a minister, his family, seminary education, WWII, his marriage, ministry appointments and residences. 3 tapes, 270 mins., 68 pp. 
Interview by Eugenia Eberle, 1991 
Donated by Eugenia Eberle 
OPEN 
See collateral file: interviewer's notes, photos, and transcript of a sermon.  
  
